doctors in san francisco are debating whether a prison inmate with only one kidney should be permitted to donate that organ to his daughter . by doing so , david patterson would put his own life in jeopardy . he would need kidney dialysis while serving the final three years of his prison sentence . 16-year-old renada daniel patterson desperately needs this transplant , because the kidney her father gave her two years ago is now failing . her mother is hoping someone else will come forward . 